#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an3.53"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an3.53:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 3 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 3 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.53:0.2"
msgid "6. Brāhmaṇavagga "
msgstr "6. Brahmins "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an3.53:0.3"
msgid "53. Aññatarabrāhmaṇasutta "
msgstr "53. A Certain Brahmin "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an3.53:1.1"
msgid "Atha kho aññataro brāhmaṇo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi … pe … ekamantaṃ nisinno kho so brāhmaṇo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then a brahmin went up to the Buddha, and exchanged greetings with him. Seated to one side he said to the Buddha: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.53:1.2"
msgid "“‘sandiṭṭhiko dhammo sandiṭṭhiko dhammo’ti, bho gotama, vuccati. "
msgstr "“Master Gotama, they speak of ‘a teaching visible in this very life’. "

#. VAR: opaneyyiko → opanayiko (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an3.53:1.3"
msgid "Kittāvatā nu kho, bho gotama, sandiṭṭhiko dhammo hoti akāliko ehipassiko opaneyyiko paccattaṃ veditabbo viññūhī”ti? "
msgstr "In what way is the teaching visible in this very life, immediately effective, inviting inspection, relevant, so that sensible people can know it for themselves?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.157, sc2
msgctxt "an3.53:2.1"
msgid "“Ratto kho, brāhmaṇa, rāgena abhibhūto pariyādinnacitto attabyābādhāyapi ceteti, parabyābādhāyapi ceteti, ubhayabyābādhāyapi ceteti, cetasikampi dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti. "
msgstr "“A greedy person, overcome and overwhelmed by greed, intends to hurt themselves, hurt others, and hurt both. They experience mental pain and sadness. "

# NOTE: Note: following section absent from BB and many pali editions.
#. VAR: etthantare pāṭho sī, syā2, syā3, kaṃ, pā1 potthakesu na dissati, idhapi
msgctxt "an3.53:2.2"
msgid "Rāge pahīne nevattabyābādhāyapi ceteti, na parabyābādhāyapi ceteti, na ubhayabyābādhāyapi ceteti, na cetasikaṃ dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti. "
msgstr "When greed has been given up, they don’t intend to hurt themselves, hurt others, and hurt both. They don’t experience mental pain and sadness. "

msgctxt "an3.53:2.3"
msgid "Ratto kho … pe … kāyena duccaritaṃ carati, vācāya duccaritaṃ carati, manasā duccaritaṃ carati. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an3.53:2.4"
msgid "Rāge pahīne neva kāyena duccaritaṃ carati, na vācāya duccaritaṃ carati, na manasā duccaritaṃ carati. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an3.53:2.5"
msgid "Ratto kho … pe … attatthampi yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti, paratthampi yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti, ubhayatthampi yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an3.53:2.6"
msgid "Rāge pahīne attatthampi yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, paratthampi yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ubhayatthampi yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an3.53:2.7"
msgid "Evampi kho, brāhmaṇa, sandiṭṭhiko dhammo hoti … pe …. "
msgstr "This is how the teaching is visible in this very life, immediately effective, inviting inspection, relevant, so that sensible people can know it for themselves. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an3.53:3.1"
msgid "Duṭṭho kho, brāhmaṇa, dosena abhibhūto pariyādinnacitto attabyābādhāyapi ceteti, parabyābādhāyapi ceteti, ubhayabyābādhāyapi ceteti, cetasikampi dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti. "
msgstr "A hateful person, overcome by hate, intends to hurt themselves, hurt others, and hurt both. They experience mental pain and sadness. "

#. VAR: na cetasikampi → na cetasikaṃ (bj, s1-3, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "an3.53:3.2"
msgid "Dose pahīne nevattabyābādhāyapi ceteti, na parabyābādhāyapi ceteti, na ubhayabyābādhāyapi ceteti, na cetasikampi dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti. "
msgstr "When hate has been given up, they don’t intend to hurt themselves, hurt others, and hurt both. They don’t experience mental pain and sadness. "

msgctxt "an3.53:3.3"
msgid "Evampi kho, brāhmaṇa, sandiṭṭhiko dhammo hoti … pe …. "
msgstr "This, too, is how the teaching is visible in this very life, immediately effective, inviting inspection, relevant, so that sensible people can know it for themselves. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an3.53:4.1"
msgid "Mūḷho kho, brāhmaṇa, mohena abhibhūto pariyādinnacitto attabyābādhāyapi ceteti, parabyābādhāyapi ceteti, ubhayabyābādhāyapi ceteti, cetasikampi dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti. "
msgstr "A deluded person, overcome by delusion, intends to hurt themselves, hurt others, and hurt both. They experience mental pain and sadness. "

msgctxt "an3.53:4.2"
msgid "Mohe pahīne nevattabyābādhāyapi ceteti, na parabyābādhāyapi ceteti, na ubhayabyābādhāyapi ceteti, na cetasikaṃ dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti. "
msgstr "When delusion has been given up, they don’t intend to hurt themselves, hurt others, and hurt both. They don’t experience mental pain and sadness. "

msgctxt "an3.53:4.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, brāhmaṇa, sandiṭṭhiko dhammo hoti akāliko ehipassiko opaneyyiko paccattaṃ veditabbo viññūhī”ti. "
msgstr "This, too, is how the teaching is visible in this very life, immediately effective, inviting inspection, relevant, so that sensible people can know it for themselves.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "an3.53:5.1"
msgid "“Abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama, abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama. "
msgstr "“Excellent, Master Gotama! Excellent! "

msgctxt "an3.53:5.2"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bho gotama, nikkujjitaṃ vā ukkujjeyya, paṭicchannaṃ vā vivareyya, mūḷhassa vā maggaṃ ācikkheyya, andhakāre vā telapajjotaṃ dhāreyya: ‘cakkhumanto rūpāni dakkhantī’ti; evamevaṃ bhotā gotamena anekapariyāyena dhammo pakāsito. "
msgstr "As if he were righting the overturned, or revealing the hidden, or pointing out the path to the lost, or lighting a lamp in the dark so people with good eyes can see what’s there, Master Gotama has made the teaching clear in many ways. "

msgctxt "an3.53:5.3"
msgid "Esāhaṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāmi dhammañca bhikkhusaṅghañca. "
msgstr "I go for refuge to Master Gotama, to the teaching, and to the mendicant Saṅgha. "

msgctxt "an3.53:5.4"
msgid "Upāsakaṃ maṃ bhavaṃ gotamo dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti. "
msgstr "From this day forth, may Master Gotama remember me as a lay follower who has gone for refuge for life.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an3.53:5.5"
msgid "Tatiyaṃ. "
msgstr ""

